      • getAll

        public Set<H> getAll(Type t)
        Description copied from interface: TypeMap
        Get all Objects associated to all unrelated compatible types. for example we habe Object O of type T a subtype of T1 and T2. if this typemap contains Objects mapped to T1 and T2, those 2 objects will be returned if T1 and T2 are not related (subtypes of each other) if T1 extends T2 the obeject mapped to the most specific type is returned.
